## ⚠️ Critical Integration Points for Merging

> [!IMPORTANT]
> These are the key coupling points to pay attention to during the merge.

### 1. Dual Backend Problem
- `budget-bandhu-rag/` runs on `:8000` — the main API server
- `budget-bandhu-models/` has its own [api/main.py](file:///Users/aditya4/Desktop/Budget-Bandhu/budget-bandhu-rag/api/main.py) with [ml_routes.py](file:///Users/aditya4/Desktop/Budget-Bandhu/budget-bandhu-models/api/ml_routes.py) — designed to run as a separate ML microservice on `:8001`
- **Current state:** ML models are wired via `intelligence/ml_client.py` in the RAG backend (calls `:8001`), but falls back gracefully if unavailable

### 2. Shared Model Code Duplication
- `budget-bandhu-rag/intelligence/` has local copies of some intelligence modules
- `budget-bandhu-models/intelligence/` has the canonical ML model code
- `budget-bandhu-rag/core/agent_controller.py` ≠ `budget-bandhu-rag/api/core/agent_controller.py` — duplicate controller files

### 3. Frontend User Identity Split
- Goals page uses wallet address (MetaMask) as `user_id`
- Other pages may use email/username as user identity
- Fallback: `demo_user_001` if no wallet saved

### 4. Environment Variables Scattered
- 3 separate `.env` files across frontend/backend/web3
- Private keys, API URLs, contract addresses need to stay in sync

